File: Al Ahly head coach Pitso Mosimane.Â Khaled DESOUKI / AFP JOHANNESBURG - After lengthy negotiations, Al Ahly and Pitso Mosimane have finally agreed on a contract extension. Mosimane has signed on for another two years. The highly successful South African now stays at Africa's Club of the 20th Century. His deal follows Ahly's impressive bronze win at the Fifa Club World Cup in Qatar last month. While details of the new contract have not been released, it's reported the coach will earn around R2.5-million per month.